      "file_path": "cps-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/utils/YangParserHelper.java",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 125,
      "message": "1) technically the old wording was more correct. I don't think an IO error is a 'validation' error. But I suppose it is doen to 'personal interpretation'\n\n2) I suppose the big change is you are removing the data from the exception which is probably a good thing. Maybe log the data at debug level for trouble shooting purposes...",
